Date: 6 Mar 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC [edited

As restrictions on the movement of some livestock is lifted, 2 more cases
of Foot-and-Mouth Disease (FMD) have been confirmed in the UK. Both the new
cases are in Cumbria and are linked to the initial outbreak.
Chronology to date, cumulative number of herds/flocks affected:
21 Feb: 1
22 Feb: 3
23 Feb: 5
24 Feb: 6
25 Feb: 7
26 Feb: 12
27 Feb: 17
28 Feb: 24
1 Mar: 31
2 Mar: 40
3 Mar: 51
4 Mar: 69
5 Mar: 74
6 Mar: 76
Number of livestock scheduled for slaughter: 78 450
